s [recommendation for projects that have a `__init__.py` in the `tests` directory](https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/goodpractices.html#choosing-a-test-layout-import-rules)\r\n   - Ionel M\u0103rie\u0219's argument in his \"[Packaging a python library](https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2014/05/25/python-packaging/)\" blog post on the subject\r\n- Hynek Schlawack's \"[Testing & Packaging](https://hynek.me/articles/testing-packaging/)\" blog post\r\n- The PyPA's [summary of their recommendations given their 2019 Packaging Mini Summit](https://github.com/pypa/packaging.python.org/issues/320#issuecomment-495990983)\r\n\r\nTLDR: Use a `src` directory structure to ensure that the code that is tested is the code that is shipped in the distribution and nothing else.\r\n\r\n# Checklist Before Requesting Reviewer\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests are passing\r\n- [x] \"WIP\" removed from the title of the pull request\r\n- [x] Selected an Assignee for the PR to be responsible for the log summary\r\n\r\n# Before Merging\r\n\r\nFor the PR Assignees:\r\n\r\n- [x] Summarize commit messages into a comprehensive review of the PR\r\n\r\n```\r\n* Use a src directory for project directory structure\r\n   - Ensures that the code that is tested is the code that is shipped\r\n   - c.f.\r\n     https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/goodpractices.html#choosing-a-test-layout-import-rules\r\n     https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2014/05/25/python-packaging/\r\n* Use MANIFEST.in graft command to simplify manifest\r\n   - c.f.\r\n     https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41661616/what-is-the-graft-command-in-pythons-manifest-in-file\r\n     https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2014/06/25/python-packaging-pitfalls/\r\n* Update schema paths for deployment to docs\r\n* Remove the shebang from setup.py\r\n   - c.f. https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0394/\r\n```", "created_at": "2019-07-15T17:26:20Z", "updated_at": "2019-08-27T05:12:18Z", "closed_at": "2019-07-16T03:31:08Z", "merged_at": "2019-07-16T03:31:08Z", "merge_commit_sha": "d9a9ad13fbb6336a